  "more_content": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983418808\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" alt=\"Black and white photo of The New Yorker facade in the 30s. \" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983396/m1ylflmlwziib7s82ubj.jpg\" />What began on January 2nd, 1930 as a grand Art Deco hotel became a rich part of New York&rsquo;s history. Here are some of the highlights of The New Yorker Hotel&rsquo;s history.&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983469234\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" alt=\"Laborers working at The New Yorker Hotel construction site.\" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983453/aahi5hrxkvawrln8lnhj.jpg\" />Construction Lasted 22 Months</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">In 1928, construction for The New Yorker Hotel began. Surprisingly, the recession didn&rsquo;t stop the works and the hotel opened its doors on January 2nd, 1930. Rising 43 stories high and 78 feet deep, this new Art Deco building became an icon of New York City&rsquo;s skyline.&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983528195\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" alt=\"North section of The New Yorker Hotel lobby in the 30s.\" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983490/sy4opdiapk0ximkz7r1b.jpg\" />The New Yorker, a Hotel Unlike Any Other</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Here are a handful of amenities and perks that made The New Yorker Hotel unique. A tunnel connected directly to Penn Station, providing immediate access to the hotel for weary travelers. A power plant capable of providing for a small city of 25,000&mdash;this was in use from 1930 to 1967. Luxurious rooms that featured state-of-the-art technology of the day. The list goes on. Get more <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/fun-facts-about-the-new-yorker-hotel-part-1/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">fun facts</a> about the hotel in our <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/fun-facts-about-the-new-yorker-hotel-part-two/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">blog</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983587001\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" alt=\"Tables and dancing floor of the luxurious Terrace Room at Thew Yorker Hotel.\" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983548/slbq8cpfu7udyiyfmqdl.jpg\" />An Entertainment Hub</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Between the <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/guests-at-the-new-yorker-hotel-1930s-1960s/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">1930s and 1960s</a>, The New Yorker Hotel was THE place to go and be seen. The Terrace Room, an ice-skating rink and an NBC broadcasting station made the hotel widely popular. Not to mention that ice show and Big Band acts were the most sought-after entertainment options in the city. Read more about <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/history-of-entertainment-at-the-new-yorker-hotel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">entertainment at The New Yorker Hotel</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983365722\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" alt=\"Old Nikola Tesla at The New Yorker Hotel. \" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983352/rpyfmf6oofwo9zo7w3tp.jpg\" /></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Celebrity Spotting over the Years</h4>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">As the most technologically advanced hotel of its time, The New Yorker Hotel drew a lot of <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/five-famous-guests-at-the-new-yorker/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">attention from A-listers</a>. Some of the biggest names include Mickey Rooney, Barbara Stanwyck, Joan Crawford, Barack Obama, Sr., Benny Goodman and more. Muhammad Ali recovered from the &ldquo;Fight of the Century&rdquo; right here with us. But all-time favorite resident has to be <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/nikola-tesla-and-the-new-yorker-hotel/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Nikola Tesla</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Today is no different. Back in 2016, Hillary Clinton delivered her concession speech in the Grand Ballroom. Nowadays, the <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/manhattan-center-fun-facts-and-events/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Manhattan Center</a> hosts frequent concerts and shows that bring together top contemporary artists. And, of course, the canine elites walk through our doors during the Westminster Dog Show.&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><img id=\"1577983662344\" class=\" \" src=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" alt=\"The New Yorker Hotel facade in the 70s.\" data-image-large=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_1200,w_1200/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" data-image-medium=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_992,w_992/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" data-image-small=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_768,w_768/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" data-image-xsmall=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fit,h_300,w_300/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" data-image-thumb=\"//res.cloudinary.com/traveltripperweb/image/upload/c_fill,g_faces,h_140,w_140/v1577983648/lzfhg0gnri0hj4jdi2uw.jpg\" /></p>\n<h4 dir=\"ltr\">Rising from Darkness</h4>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Although The New Yorker Hotel had an interesting first 30 years of life, to say the least, when the decade of the 70s hit, everything changed. In 1972, the inner city decline pushed the hotel to close its doors. Between 1976 and 1980, The New Yorker undergoes a restoration handled by the Unification Church, who sought to turn it into a mission center for the Korean religious movement. Once the 90s arrived, <a href=\"https://www.newyorkerhotel.com/blog/the-new-yorker-hotel-a-unique-experience/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">The New Yorker Hotel</a> was reintroduced into the hospitality industry. After another massive renovation that restored its Art Deco heritage, the hotel became what it is today.&nbsp;</p>",
